        <div class="accordion-content">
            <header>
                <span class="title">Why one need to join the clubs?</span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
            </header>

            <p class="description">
            Joining clubs allows you to meet new people who share your interests and passions, develop new skills, and build
            a sense
            of community within your school or organization.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-content">
            <header>
                <span class="title">Can I join more than 3 clubs, is there any limit for the clubs?</span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
            </header>

            <p class="description">
        While there may not be a specific limit, it's important to prioritize your commitments. Joining a few niche clubs
        that
        align with your interests will allow you to make the most of your experience and develop meaningful connections.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
            <header>
                <span class="title">Can I start my own club at college?</span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
            </header>

            <p class="description">
        Yes, students can start their own club if it's not yet found, you will typically need to find a
        faculty advisor and follow guidelines or procedures outlined by our NIT Andhra Pradesh.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
            <header>
                <span class="title">How much time should I dedicate to my club involvement ?</span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
            </header>

            <p class="description">
            It depends on your personal goals and commitments, but it's important to balance your involvement in clubs with
            your academic and personal responsibilities. Try to find a few niche clubs that align with your interests and passions, and
            commit to those clubs fully.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content">
            <header>
                <span class="title">How can I find clubs that align with my interests?</span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
            </header>
        
            <p class="description">
            One way to find clubs is to attend club fairs or events hosted by your school or organization. Additionally, you
            can
            check online directories or social media platforms to discover new clubs that match your interests.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>const accordionContent = document.querySelectorAll(".accordion-content");

        accordionContent.forEach((item, index) => {
            let header = item.querySelector("header");
            header.addEventListener("click", () => {
                item.classList.toggle("open");

                let description = item.querySelector(".description");
                if (item.classList.contains("open")) {
                    description.style.height = `${description.scrollHeight}px`; //scrollHeight property returns the height of an element including padding , but excluding borders, scrollbar or margin
                    item.querySelector("i").classList.replace("fa-plus", "fa-minus");
                } else {
                    description.style.height = "0px";
                    item.querySelector("i").classList.replace("fa-minus", "fa-plus");
                }
                removeOpen(index); //calling the funtion and also passing the index number of the clicked header
            })
        })

        function removeOpen(index1) {
            accordionContent.forEach((item2, index2) => {
                if (index1 != index2) {
                    item2.classList.remove("open");

                    let des = item2.querySelector(".description");
                    des.style.height = "0px";
                    item2.querySelector("i").classList.replace("fa-minus", "fa-plus");
                }
            })
        }</script>
